    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of Chinese porcelain wares of the Qing dynasty with a black ground covered by transparent green enamel. Represents a subset of the "famille verte" class of enamel ware style designated by Albert Jacquemart in the 19th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
